const e="Projects",t="Here are some of my projects. They are hosted on various platforms such as **Github Pages**, **Vercel** and **Cloudflare Pages**.",o={desc:'**Keyboard** is a simple virtual instrument that you can play using your keyboard, mouse or mobile. It uses [smplr](https://github.com/danigb/smplr "smplr is a collection of sampled instruments for Web Audio API ready to be used with no setup required.") for the audio samples.'},s={desc:"**Grafikverktyg2022** is an app I made to create color palettes that could then easily be imported into Figma. It also allows you to send the colors to [uicolors.app](https://uicolors.app/)."},i={desc:"**Tutorials** is a blog where I post things that I want to reference later. It includes posts where I learned Svelte from a Svelte course made by Li Hau Tan that was on the freecodecamp youtube channel as well as workflow improvements for VSCode."},a={title:e,introduction:t,keyboard:o,"branschdag-2023-03":{desc:"**Branschdag-23-03** is an app I made to simplify finding the companies at the Nackademin 'branschdag' event. You can click on the classrooms to see which companies are in there, filter by your subject to only view companies that are interesting to you and click the companies' names to see their information."},Grafikverktyg2022:s,Tutorials:i,"henrikvilhelmberglund.github.io":{desc:`**henrikvilhelmberglund.github.io** is my portfolio site and the site you are reading right now. I'm using a custom domain so the URL is slightly different. On this site I list some of my projects and link to my socials. This project was my first time using "real" i18n using [sveltekit-i18n](https://github.com/sveltekit-i18n/lib) and the VSCode extension [i18n-ally](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=lokalise.i18n-ally). `}};export{s as Grafikverktyg2022,i as Tutorials,a as default,t as introduction,o as keyboard,e as title};
